​Card 3: The "Presence" (Profile & Availability)
​This is the management card. It controls how the tutor appears to the world.
​What it does: It houses the "Online/Offline" toggle and the weekly availability grid.
​The Strategy: Instead of burying availability in a deep settings menu, putting it on the main hub allows a tutor to quickly "Go Offline" if they have a sudden exam or personal emergency.
​Less Work: It also shows the modules they are currently "Certified" to teach, allowing them to add or remove subjects based on their confidence level.




​Card 4: The "Vault" (Combined Analytics & Records)
​This is the passive card. It’s the "simple data" powerhouse we discussed.
​The Design: This is the only card that is purely informative. No buttons to click (except "Download"), no graphs to decipher.
​The Content: It’s a tabbed ledger. One tab for History (who, when, where), one tab for Ratings (the "vibe check" from students), and one tab for Stats (the total hours count).
